Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma scored an unbeaten 102 off 62 balls
Shubman Gill scored 51 in a hundred-run stand with Rohit
Virat Kohli scored an unbeaten 122 off 94 balls
Jasprit Bumrah took 5 wickets for 14 runs
Ravindra Jadeja's introduction brought Rohit Sharma success, removing Roelof van der Merwe first ball
Pre-Game Insights: Experts predicted India as the favorites given their home advantage
India captain Rohit Sharma said they go in unchanged and expressed themselves with freedom from Day 1 in the tournament
Scott Edwards, Netherlands skipper, said they would have batted too and adds they too are fielding the same XI as the one that played against England
Post-Match Reflections: Hardik Pandya expressed pride in the team's resilience after a close win
Rohit Sharma remarked that winning the series was a significant morale booster ahead of the World Cup
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play, reducing the game to 20 overs per side
India ended their ICC trophy drought, winning their first title since 2013
Teja Nidamanuru smashed six sixes to hit a quickfire fifty
Engelbrecht's vigil ended with a fighting 45, the most for Netherlands at this edition
Van Beek and van der Merwe added 32 in 23 balls but were removed by Kuldeep Yadav and Ravindra Jadeja
